# 📡 Smart Network Bandwidth Monitor

# Project Description

Smart Network Bandwidth Monitor is a Python-based system monitoring tool that tracks internet usage in real-time. The project helps users identify which applications are consuming internet bandwidth, monitor upload and download speeds, and analyze network performance through visual graphs.

Slow internet connection is a common problem faced by students and professionals. Often, background applications consume network bandwidth without the user's knowledge. This project solves this issue by providing real-time monitoring and visualization of network usage.

The system continuously collects network data from the computer and displays upload and download speed along with graphical representation. This helps users understand network behavior and detect unusual usage patterns.

