# Technologies Used

The project is developed using Python and the following libraries:

### Python

Python is used as the main programming language because it supports system-level programming and real-time monitoring.

### Streamlit

Streamlit is used to build the user interface and display live network data.

### Psutil

Psutil is used to collect system and network usage information.

### Pandas

Pandas is used for storing and managing real-time data.

### Matplotlib

Matplotlib is used for plotting graphs and visualizing network usage.

---

# How the Project Works

The project works in the following steps:

### Step 1: Network Data Collection

The system collects:

• Bytes sent
• Bytes received
• Upload speed
• Download speed

This is done using the psutil library.

---

### Step 2: Speed Calculation

The system calculates:

Upload Speed = Bytes Sent Difference / Time
Download Speed = Bytes Received Difference / Time

This provides real-time network speed.

---

### Step 3: Data Storage

The system stores:

• Time
• Upload speed
• Download speed

This data is stored in a dataframe.

---

### Step 4: Visualization

The system generates:

• Real-time graphs
• Speed trends
• Network usage charts

This helps users analyze network performance.

